def plotFitOverHist(df, t):
    tmin, tmax = min(df), max(df)
    space = np.linspace(tmin, tmax, len(df))
    m = df.mean()
    s = df.std()
    pdf = stats.norm.pdf(space, m, s)
    plt.hist(df, normed = True, alpha=.3)
    plt.plot(space, pdf, label="Norm", color='r')
    plt.title(t)
    plt.show()

plotFitOverHist(dfIdle.Degrees, 'Idle Gaussian Fit')
plotFitOverHist(dfLeft.Degrees, 'Left Turns Gaussian Fit')
plotFitOverHist(dfRight.Degrees, 'Right Turns Gaussian Fit')

## Plot GPS tracks
gpsData = pd.DataFrame.from_csv('danusha-gps.csv', parse_dates=False)
lats = gpsData['Lat'].values
longs = gpsData['Long'].values
lats = filter(lambda t: -90 < t < 90, lats)
longs = filter(lambda t: t != -9999, longs)

m = Basemap(llcrnrlon=min(longs) - .001,llcrnrlat=min(lats) - .001,urcrnrlon=max(longs) + .001,urcrnrlat=max(lats) + .001,lat_ts=20,
            resolution='c',projection='merc',lon_0=longs[0],lat_0=lats[0])

x1, y1 = m(longs, lats)
m.drawmapboundary(fill_color='white')
m.scatter(x1, y1, s=100, c='r', marker="o")

objects = ('Segment 1', 'Segment 2', 'Segment 3', 'Segment 4')
y_pos = np.arange(len(objects))
detected = [2, 2, 3, 3]
notDetected = [1, 1, 0, 0]

plt.ylim(0, 4)
plt.bar(y_pos, detected, align='center', alpha=0.5, linewidth=0, width = 0.5)
plt.bar(y_pos, notDetected, align='center', alpha=0.5, color='#d2d2d2', linewidth=0, width = 0.5, bottom = detected)
plt.xticks(y_pos, objects)
plt.yticks(np.arange(0, 4, 1))
plt.ylabel('Detections')
plt.legend(['Detected', 'Not Detected'])
